Date: Mon, 27 Apr 1998 13:25:42 -0400
From: Nelson, Ann M. <NELSONA@afip.osd.mil>

Without clinical history for the human or the dogs, it is hard to make even
a good differential diagnosis. However, according the Department of
Veterinary Pathology here at the Institute, there are some strains of rabies
with a prolonged incubation at the bite site.
--
Ann Marie Nelson, M.D.
Chief, Division of AIDS Pathology
and Emerging Infectious Disease
